The paper proposes a framework for automatically completing tables using a heterogeneous knowledge base, which involves integrating natural language contextual information with schema-specific structural information. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories related to databases (cs.DB), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), information retrieval (cs.IR), computational linguistics (cs.CL), and machine learning (cs.LG).
